wikipedia_page.main: Janet Douglas (died after 1678), was a Scottish woman who claimed to have second sight.

response: * Janet Douglas (diplomat) (born 1960), British diplomat and ambassador
* Janet Douglas, 17th-century Scottish woman who claimed to have second sight
* Janet Douglas, Lady Glamis (died 1537), Scottish noblewoman falsely accused of witchcraft and burnt to death
